  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is conducted to evaluate the effectivity of hypertonic dextrose spray as an&#xD;
      endoscopic topical hemostatic agent, compared to conventional agent (adrenaline injection,&#xD;
      followed by hemoclip or thermocoagulation), in patients with acute non-variceal upper GI&#xD;
      bleeding.&#xD;
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
